  "description": "The biological bioluminescence of an electric eel colony in the reef — not random storm but organized, biological electrical discharge. Noise src1 through BP (proc1=BP, 1200 Hz, reso=0.72) creates the base electrical charge. src2=Sine (Type=1) at root, srcMix=0.22 — the tonal center of the organism underneath the electrical noise. proc2=LP (3500 Hz) keeps the shine. gestureMode=3, flashTrigger=0.72. Poly4 — multiple organisms discharging simultaneously. LFO->FilterCutoff (1.2 Hz, the discharge rhythm), Env->Volume, Velocity->FilterReso, Aftertouch->FXMix. aggression=0.62 — controlled, biological, not chaotic. MOVEMENT 0.35, CHARACTER 0.45.",
